---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---

<BaseLayout title="Install / Getting Started">
  <section>
    <h2>Install & build</h2>

    <p class="lead">Get ReadForge running locally, or build release artifacts from source.</p>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Prerequisites</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Flutter SDK 3.10.1+</li>
        <li>Dart 3.10.1+</li>
        <li>Java 17+ (Android builds)</li>
        <li>Android Studio / Android SDK (Android device or emulator)</li>
        <li>Node 18+ (only if you work on the website in <code>astro/</code>)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Clone the repository</h3>
      <pre>git clone https://github.com/cmwen/read-forge-app.git
    cd read-forge-app</pre>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Run locally</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Get dependencies: <code>flutter pub get</code></li>
        <li>Run: <code>flutter run</code></li>
        <li>Optionally specify a device:</li>
      </ol>
      <pre>flutter run -d android</pre>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Build release artifacts</h3>
      <pre>flutter build apk         # Android APK
    flutter build appbundle   # Play Store (AAB)</pre>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Run tests</h3>
      <pre>flutter test
    flutter test --coverage</pre>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Website (optional)</h3>
      <p>If you need to work on the repository website, switch to the <code>astro/</code> directory and run:</p>
      <pre>cd astro
    npm install
    npm run dev</pre>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Need more help?</h3>
      <p>Open an issue or pull request on <a href="https://github.com/cmwen/read-forge-app" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>. For CI or release problems, check <code>.github/workflows/</code>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
